
# 🧠 Linux + Git + GDB Cheat Sheet

---

# 🐧 Linux Basics

## Navigation

```bash
pwd                 # show current directory
ls                  # list files
ls -la              # detailed list (hidden files too)
cd <dir>            # change directory
cd ..               # go back one folder
mkdir <name>        # create folder
rmdir <name>        # remove empty folder
rm -r <name>        # remove folder recursively
```

---

## File Operations

```bash
touch file.txt      # create empty file
cp a b              # copy file
mv a b              # move/rename file
rm file.txt         # delete file
cat file.txt        # print file content
less file.txt       # scroll file (q to quit)
head file.txt       # first 10 lines
tail file.txt       # last 10 lines
```

---

## Search / Text Processing

```bash
grep "text" file.txt            # search in file
grep -R "text" .                # recursive search in folder
find . -name "*.c"             # find files by name
```

---

## System / Processes

```bash
ps aux              # list processes
top                 # live process monitor
kill <pid>          # kill process
kill -9 <pid>       # force kill
```

---

## Networking Basics

```bash
ping google.com     # test internet connection
curl example.com    # fetch webpage
ip a                # show network interfaces
ss -tuln            # list open ports
```

---

## Permissions

```bash
chmod +x file      # make executable
chmod 644 file     # set permissions
chown user file    # change owner
```

---

# 📦 Git Basics

## Setup

```bash
git init
git config --global user.name "name"
git config --global user.email "email"
```

---

## Workflow

```bash
git status
git add file.c
git add .
git commit -m "message"
git log
```

---

## Branching

```bash
git branch
git branch new-branch
git checkout new-branch
git checkout main
git merge new-branch
```

---

## Remote (GitHub)

```bash
git remote add origin <url>
git push -u origin main
git pull
git clone <url>
```

---

# 🐛 GDB Debugger

## Basic flow

```bash
gcc -g file.c -o app   # compile with debug symbols
gdb ./app              # start debugger
```

---

## Inside GDB

```gdb
run                 # start program
break main          # set breakpoint
break file.c:10     # breakpoint at line
next                # step over
step                # step into
continue            # continue execution
print x             # print variable
backtrace           # show call stack
quit                # exit
```

---

## Debug mindset

* `break` → pause execution
* `next` → move line by line
* `step` → go inside function
* `print` → inspect reality
* `backtrace` → understand how you got here
